{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1023,"text":"As a boy in Lima,"},{"time":2690,"text":"my grandfather told me a legend"},{"time":4825,"text":"of the Spanish conquest of Peru."},{"time":8007,"text":"Atahualpa, emperor of the Inca,\nhad been captured and killed."},{"time":11570,"text":"Pizarro and his conquistadors\nhad grown rich,"},{"time":14577,"text":"and tales of their conquest\nand glory had reached Spain"},{"time":17787,"text":"and was bringing new waves of Spaniards,\nhungry for gold and glory."},{"time":24055,"text":"They would go into towns and ask the Inca,"},{"time":26977,"text":"\"Where's another civilization\nwe can conquer? Where's more gold?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":30776,"text":"And the Inca, out of vengeance, told them,"},{"time":34648,"text":"\"Go to the Amazon."},{"time":36767,"text":"You'll find all the gold you want there."},{"time":39437,"text":"In fact, there is a city called Paititi --\nEl Dorado in Spanish --"},{"time":44175,"text":"made entirely of gold.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":47303,"text":"The Spanish set off into the jungle,"},{"time":49223,"text":"but the few that return\ncome back with stories,"},{"time":53904,"text":"stories of powerful shamans,"},{"time":57735,"text":"of warriors with poisoned arrows,"},{"time":60663,"text":"of trees so tall they blotted out the sun,"},{"time":64465,"text":"spiders that ate birds,\nsnakes that swallowed men whole"},{"time":69241,"text":"and a river that boiled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73795,"text":"All this became a childhood memory."},{"time":75803,"text":"And years passed."},{"time":76986,"text":"I'm working on my PhD at SMU,"},{"time":79485,"text":"trying to understand\nPeru's geothermal energy potential,"},{"time":83413,"text":"when I remember this legend,"},{"time":85483,"text":"and I began asking that question."},{"time":88316,"text":"Could the boiling river exist?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92140,"text":"I asked colleagues from universities,"},{"time":94363,"text":"the government,"},{"time":95544,"text":"oil, gas and mining companies,"},{"time":97061,"text":"and the answer was a unanimous no."},{"time":100459,"text":"And this makes sense."},{"time":103070,"text":"You see, boiling rivers\ndo exist in the world,"},{"time":105722,"text":"but they're generally\nassociated with volcanoes."},{"time":108649,"text":"You need a powerful heat source"},{"time":110820,"text":"to produce such a large\ngeothermal manifestation."},{"time":114210,"text":"And as you can see from the red dots\nhere, which are volcanoes,"},{"time":119438,"text":"we don't have volcanoes in the Amazon,"},{"time":122280,"text":"nor in most of Peru."},{"time":124122,"text":"So it follows: We should not expect\nto see a boiling river."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129660,"text":"Telling this same story\nat a family dinner,"},{"time":133772,"text":"my aunt tells me,"},{"time":136266,"text":"\"But no, Andrés, I've been there.\nI've swum in that river.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":140898,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144559,"text":"Then my uncle jumps in."},{"time":146330,"text":"\"No, Andrés, she's not kidding."},{"time":149084,"text":"You see, you can only swim in it\nafter a very heavy rain,"},{"time":153091,"text":"and it's protected by a powerful shaman."},{"time":156361,"text":"Your aunt, she's friends with his wife.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":159257,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161086,"text":"\"¿Cómo?\" [\"Huh?\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162261,"text":"You know, despite all\nmy scientific skepticism,"},{"time":164499,"text":"I found myself hiking into the jungle,\nguided by my aunt,"},{"time":168955,"text":"over 700 kilometers away\nfrom the nearest volcanic center,"},{"time":172876,"text":"and well, honestly,\nmentally preparing myself"},{"time":176518,"text":"to behold the legendary\n\"warm stream of the Amazon.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":182671,"text":"But then ..."},{"time":184316,"text":"I heard something,"},{"time":187255,"text":"a low surge"},{"time":190347,"text":"that got louder and louder"},{"time":193792,"text":"as we came closer."},{"time":196300,"text":"It sounded like ocean waves\nconstantly crashing,"},{"time":200252,"text":"and as we got closer, I saw smoke, vapor,\ncoming up through the trees."},{"time":204961,"text":"And then, I saw this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209791,"text":"I immediately grabbed for my thermometer,"},{"time":212284,"text":"and the average temperatures in the river"},{"time":215585,"text":"were 86 degrees C."},{"time":219540,"text":"This is not quite\nthe 100-degree C boiling"},{"time":222831,"text":"but definitely close enough."},{"time":226296,"text":"The river flowed hot and fast."},{"time":230181,"text":"I followed it upriver and was led by,\nactually, the shaman's apprentice"},{"time":233853,"text":"to the most sacred site on the river."},{"time":235661,"text":"And this is what's bizarre --"},{"time":237091,"text":"It starts off as a cold stream."},{"time":239502,"text":"And here, at this site,"},{"time":241763,"text":"is the home of the Yacumama,"},{"time":243954,"text":"mother of the waters,\na giant serpent spirit"},{"time":247321,"text":"who births hot and cold water."},{"time":250015,"text":"And here we find a hot spring,"},{"time":254451,"text":"mixing with cold stream water\nunderneath her protective motherly jaws"},{"time":259833,"text":"and thus bringing their legends to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264283,"text":"The next morning, I woke up and --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":266285,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268528,"text":"I asked for tea."},{"time":270583,"text":"I was handed a mug, a tea bag"},{"time":272847,"text":"and, well, pointed towards the river."},{"time":276075,"text":"To my surprise, the water was clean\nand had a pleasant taste,"},{"time":280608,"text":"which is a little weird\nfor geothermal systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284441,"text":"What was amazing"},{"time":286013,"text":"is that the locals had always\nknown about this place,"},{"time":289021,"text":"and that I was by no means\nthe first outsider to see it."},{"time":293701,"text":"It was just part of their everyday life."},{"time":297115,"text":"They drink its water."},{"time":299833,"text":"They take in its vapor."},{"time":302412,"text":"They cook with it,"},{"time":304127,"text":"clean with it,"},{"time":305661,"text":"even make their medicines with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309094,"text":"I met the shaman,"},{"time":310864,"text":"and he seemed like an extension\nof the river and his jungle."},{"time":315848,"text":"He asked for my intentions"},{"time":318609,"text":"and listened carefully."},{"time":321262,"text":"Then, to my tremendous relief --"},{"time":324397,"text":"I was freaking out,\nto be honest with you --"},{"time":327968,"text":"a smile began to snake across his face,\nand he just laughed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332271,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335796,"text":"I had received the shaman's blessing\nto study the river,"},{"time":340415,"text":"on the condition that after I take\nthe water samples"},{"time":343843,"text":"and analyze them in my lab,"},{"time":345383,"text":"wherever I was in the world,"},{"time":348265,"text":"that I pour the waters\nback into the ground"},{"time":352055,"text":"so that, as the shaman said,"},{"time":354126,"text":"the waters could find their way back home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359272,"text":"I've been back every year\nsince that first visit in 2011,"},{"time":362883,"text":"and the fieldwork has been exhilarating,"},{"time":366332,"text":"demanding and at times dangerous."},{"time":370913,"text":"One story was even featured\nin National Geographic Magazine."},{"time":374152,"text":"I was trapped on a small rock\nabout the size of a sheet of paper"},{"time":378263,"text":"in sandals and board shorts,"},{"time":380327,"text":"in between an 80 degree C river"},{"time":382757,"text":"and a hot spring that, well,\nlooked like this, close to boiling."},{"time":387070,"text":"And on top of that,\nit was Amazon rain forest."},{"time":391206,"text":"Pshh, pouring rain, couldn't see a thing."},{"time":393736,"text":"The temperature differential\nmade it all white. It was a whiteout."},{"time":398956,"text":"Intense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402158,"text":"Now, after years of work,"},{"time":404620,"text":"I'll soon be submitting my geophysical\nand geochemical studies for publication."},{"time":411047,"text":"And I'd like to share, today,\nwith all of you here, on the TED stage,"},{"time":415046,"text":"for the first time,\nsome of these discoveries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419340,"text":"Well, first off, it's not a legend."},{"time":422468,"text":"Surprise!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423666,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":426015,"text":"When I first started the research,"},{"time":428553,"text":"the satellite imagery was too\nlow-resolution to be meaningful."},{"time":431556,"text":"There were just no good maps."},{"time":433754,"text":"Thanks to the support\nof the Google Earth team,"},{"time":436169,"text":"I now have this."},{"time":439251,"text":"Not only that, the indigenous name\nof the river, Shanay-timpishka,"},{"time":445538,"text":"\"boiled with the heat of the sun,\""},{"time":449540,"text":"indicating that I'm not the first\nto wonder why the river boils,"},{"time":454943,"text":"and showing that humanity\nhas always sought to explain"},{"time":458194,"text":"the world around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461526,"text":"So why does the river boil?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463948,"text":"(Bubbling sounds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":468385,"text":"It actually took me three years\nto get that footage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472879,"text":"Fault-fed hot springs."},{"time":475625,"text":"As we have hot blood running\nthrough our veins and arteries,"},{"time":479282,"text":"so, too, the earth has hot water\nrunning through its cracks and faults."},{"time":485162,"text":"Where these arteries come to the surface,\nthese earth arteries,"},{"time":488781,"text":"we'll get geothermal manifestations:"},{"time":491179,"text":"fumaroles, hot springs\nand in our case, the boiling river."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496459,"text":"What's truly incredible, though,\nis the scale of this place."},{"time":501221,"text":"Next time you cross the road,\nthink about this."},{"time":504527,"text":"The river flows wider than a two-lane road"},{"time":507223,"text":"along most of its path."},{"time":509674,"text":"It flows hot for 6.24 kilometers."},{"time":516223,"text":"Truly impressive."},{"time":519077,"text":"There are thermal pools\nlarger than this TED stage,"},{"time":522101,"text":"and that waterfall that you see there"},{"time":524601,"text":"is six meters tall --"},{"time":527384,"text":"and all with near-boiling water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532243,"text":"We mapped the temperatures\nalong the river,"},{"time":534323,"text":"and this was by far the most\ndemanding part of the fieldwork."},{"time":537866,"text":"And the results were just awesome."},{"time":541577,"text":"Sorry -- the geoscientist\nin me coming out."},{"time":544754,"text":"And it showed this amazing trend."},{"time":547204,"text":"You see, the river starts off cold."},{"time":549444,"text":"It then heats up, cools back down,\nheats up, cools back down,"},{"time":552463,"text":"heats up again, and then has\nthis beautiful decay curve"},{"time":555105,"text":"until it smashes into this cold river."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558539,"text":"Now, I understand not all of you\nare geothermal scientists,"},{"time":561357,"text":"so to put it in more everyday terms:"},{"time":564225,"text":"Everyone loves coffee."},{"time":566382,"text":"Yes? Good."},{"time":568517,"text":"Your regular cup of coffee, 54 degrees C,"},{"time":572224,"text":"an extra-hot one, well, 60."},{"time":574896,"text":"So, put in coffee shop terms,"},{"time":577091,"text":"the boiling river plots like this."},{"time":580401,"text":"There you have your hot coffee."},{"time":582906,"text":"Here you have your extra-hot coffee,"},{"time":584654,"text":"and you can see\nthat there's a bit point there"},{"time":586852,"text":"where the river is still hotter\nthan even the extra-hot coffee."},{"time":589864,"text":"And these are average water temperatures."},{"time":591880,"text":"We took these in the dry season to ensure\nthe purest geothermal temperatures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596603,"text":"But there's a magic number here\nthat's not being shown,"},{"time":599247,"text":"and that number is 47 degrees C,"},{"time":602856,"text":"because that's where things start to hurt,"},{"time":605402,"text":"and I know this from very\npersonal experience."},{"time":610186,"text":"Above that temperature,\nyou don't want to get in that water."},{"time":613036,"text":"You need to be careful."},{"time":614722,"text":"It can be deadly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616704,"text":"I've seen all sorts of animals fall in,"},{"time":619019,"text":"and what's shocking to me,\nis the process is pretty much the same."},{"time":623898,"text":"So they fall in and the first thing\nto go are the eyes."},{"time":626603,"text":"Eyes, apparently, cook very quickly.\nThey turn this milky-white color."},{"time":629994,"text":"The stream is carrying them."},{"time":631368,"text":"They're trying to swim out,\nbut their meat is cooking on the bone"},{"time":634455,"text":"because it's so hot."},{"time":635645,"text":"So they're losing power, losing power,"},{"time":637514,"text":"until finally they get to a point\nwhere hot water goes into their mouths"},{"time":640928,"text":"and they cook from the inside out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":648696,"text":"A bit sadistic, aren't we?"},{"time":650839,"text":"Jeez."},{"time":653362,"text":"Leave them marinating for a little longer."},{"time":657468,"text":"What's, again, amazing\nare these temperatures."},{"time":660220,"text":"They're similar to things that I've seen\non volcanoes all over the world"},{"time":663722,"text":"and even super-volcanoes like Yellowstone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666896,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":670173,"text":"the data is showing\nthat the boiling river exists"},{"time":675196,"text":"independent of volcanism."},{"time":678491,"text":"It's neither magmatic\nor volcanic in origin,"},{"time":683722,"text":"and again, over 700 kilometers away\nfrom the nearest volcanic center."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690543,"text":"How can a boiling river exist like this?"},{"time":695790,"text":"I've asked geothermal experts\nand volcanologists for years,"},{"time":698970,"text":"and I'm still unable to find another\nnon-volcanic geothermal system"},{"time":703811,"text":"of this magnitude."},{"time":707121,"text":"It's unique."},{"time":709489,"text":"It's special on a global scale."},{"time":714708,"text":"So, still -- how does it work?"},{"time":718460,"text":"Where do we get this heat?"},{"time":721186,"text":"There's still more research to be done"},{"time":723303,"text":"to better constrain the problem\nand better understand the system,"},{"time":726516,"text":"but from what the data is telling us now,"},{"time":728866,"text":"it looks to be the result\nof a large hydrothermal system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733151,"text":"Basically, it works like this:"},{"time":734635,"text":"So, the deeper you go\ninto the earth, the hotter it gets."},{"time":737967,"text":"We refer to this\nas the geothermal gradient."},{"time":741460,"text":"The waters could be coming\nfrom as far away as glaciers in the Andes,"},{"time":746412,"text":"then seeping down deep into the earth"},{"time":748435,"text":"and coming out to form the boiling river"},{"time":751226,"text":"after getting heated up\nfrom the geothermal gradient,"},{"time":755311,"text":"all due to this unique geologic setting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758587,"text":"Now, we found\nthat in and around the river --"},{"time":761458,"text":"this is working with colleagues"},{"time":762975,"text":"from National Geographic,\nDr. Spencer Wells,"},{"time":765086,"text":"and Dr. Jon Eisen from UC Davis --"},{"time":767820,"text":"we genetically sequenced\nthe extremophile lifeforms"},{"time":771106,"text":"living in and around the river,\nand have found new lifeforms,"},{"time":775734,"text":"unique species living\nin the boiling river."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780264,"text":"But again, despite all of these studies,\nall of these discoveries and the legends,"},{"time":786499,"text":"a question remains:"},{"time":789704,"text":"What is the significance\nof the boiling river?"},{"time":794601,"text":"What is the significance\nof this stationary cloud"},{"time":799271,"text":"that always hovers\nover this patch of jungle?"},{"time":803333,"text":"And what is the significance"},{"time":806007,"text":"of a detail in a childhood legend?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":811547,"text":"To the shaman and his community,\nit's a sacred site."},{"time":815414,"text":"To me, as a geoscientist,"},{"time":817783,"text":"it's a unique geothermal phenomenon."},{"time":822074,"text":"But to the illegal loggers\nand cattle farmers,"},{"time":825796,"text":"it's just another resource to exploit."},{"time":830820,"text":"And to the Peruvian government,\nit's just another stretch"},{"time":834631,"text":"of unprotected land ready for development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842186,"text":"My goal is to ensure\nthat whoever controls this land"},{"time":845806,"text":"understands the boiling river's\nuniqueness and significance."},{"time":850892,"text":"Because that's the question,"},{"time":853853,"text":"one of significance."},{"time":856568,"text":"And the thing there is,"},{"time":860110,"text":"we define significance."},{"time":862998,"text":"It's us. We have that power."},{"time":865682,"text":"We are the ones who draw that line"},{"time":868434,"text":"between the sacred and the trivial."},{"time":871736,"text":"And in this age,"},{"time":874036,"text":"where everything seems mapped,\nmeasured and studied,"},{"time":879290,"text":"in this age of information,"},{"time":882899,"text":"I remind you all that discoveries\nare not just made"},{"time":886495,"text":"in the black void of the unknown"},{"time":892153,"text":"but in the white noise\nof overwhelming data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897862,"text":"There remains so much to explore."},{"time":901958,"text":"We live in an incredible world."},{"time":905477,"text":"So go out."},{"time":908306,"text":"Be curious."},{"time":911711,"text":"Because we do live in a world"},{"time":915539,"text":"where shamans still sing\nto the spirits of the jungle,"},{"time":920399,"text":"where rivers do boil"},{"time":923299,"text":"and where legends do come to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927018,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928223,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}